Synopsis: Note: T|his dialogue has a lot of copies of certain branches for cinematics purposes. Do not try to condense without speaking to writer or cinematics! Lae'zel confronts a tiefling that has seen another githyanki. She tries to prise the information from him with intimidation, perhaps insisting he bow to show proper deference. Key emotions: Lae'zel is arrogant and fearsome; Zorru is afraid she will attack, but tries not to show it - at first.
